				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\triangle V}_{{non}-{rad}}=\frac{{kT}}{q}{{{{{\rm{ln}}}}}}\left (\frac{1}{{{EQE}}_{{EL}}}\right)$$\end{document}, where EQEEL is electroluminescence external quantum efficiency60. As plotted in Supplementary Fig. 25, the EQEEL values of the binary, ternary and LBL-processed ternary OSCs are 9.5 × 10−5, 1.1 × 10−4 and 2.0 × 10−4, respectively, and the corresponding ΔVnon-rads were calculated to be 0.23, 0.23, and 0.21 V. Then the ΔVrad of the solar cells could be determined, which are 0.37, 0.35 and 0.37 V for the binary, ternary and LBL-processed ternary blends, respectively. From these results, we can conclude that the introduction of the third component can afford reduced Vloss, and therefore increase the Voc of the thick devices. Additionally, LBL processing method could enable the OSCs with relatively lower ΔVnon-rad.
